<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871125-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Olin Gets Army JobsOf $110.3 MillionTo Make Munitions</HL><DD> 11/25/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD T SMF BA OLN LIT TRW ML TXN DRCOAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Olin Corp. won Army contracts totaling $110.3 million to produce munitions.    Texas Instruments Inc. received a $28.5 million Navy contract for radar systems for S-3B aircraft.    Martin Marietta Corp. was issued a $27.4 million Air Force contract for aircraft weapon-targeting equipment.    TRW Inc. was issued a $24.6 million Air Force contract for strategic-missile engineering services.    Litton Industries Inc. got an $18.2 million Army contract for navigation equipment.    Units of Boeing Co. were awarded contracts totaling $17.1 million for B-52 aircraft-engineering services for the Air Force and CH-46 helicopter equipment for the Navy.    Singer Co. won a $16.1 million Air Force contract for training services.    ATandamp;T Technologies, a unit of American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co., received a $15.1 million Navy contract for oceanographic research.    Units of McDonnell Douglas Corp. were given contracts totaling $14 million for training services for the Air Force and FA-18 aircraft test support for the Navy.    Dynamics Research Corp. said it has received a $12 million Air Force contract to continue the fourth phase of a five-year contract to develop a data collection system for the F-16 fighter aircraft. </TEXT></DOC>